GuildTask.ActivityDesc: Complete daily missions to make your contribution to the Crew.

Orienteering.ActivityDesc:
A cross-country race hosted by Banges Tech originally to promote vehicular travels. After all these years, though, the Wanderers have developed tricks that don't necessarily need a vehicle...

Race runs <green>12:00–23:00 daily</>, each starting at the top of each hour, for 12 races each day.
Pass through all <green>checkpoints</> to the finish line and complete the race.
Choose your favorite <green>vehicle</> or use your <green>unique tricks</> to finish the course!

xuanshang.ActivityDesc:
The bounty order system has been around for a very long time. After the Cataclysm, Hykros started to manage and post all the bounty orders and issue area bounty coins as rewards.
For professional bounty hunters, bounty coins are not only a type of currency but also a symbol of glory.

Wanderers can accept up to <green>4</> Bounty Missions each day.
Team up to complete the Bounty Missions to obtain <green>Bounty EXP</> and increase your <green>Bounty level</>.
The higher the Bounty level, the greater your chance to get <green>high-difficulty missions</>.

qiandao.ActivityDesc:
Welcome to Aida.
Did you sign in today?

·Sign in for a daily reward.

zuduifuben.ActivityDesc:
A high difficulty module of Hykros' training simulation. Comprising simulated battlefields that are more realistic, it aims to train warriors to fight against hostile forces with richer rewards for participants.

·Wanderers can <green>start a challenge at any time</> with no limit on challenge attempts.
·Each box costs 30 VIT to open.

Wormhole.ActivityDesc:
The Wormhole is a system Hykros created based on its research on dimensional anomalies. It provides specialized training for fighters recruited to fix the anomalies.
How long can you last in the face of the possible threats in this abnormal space?

·Wanderers can do the Wormhole challenge as many times as they want. Challenge progress resets <green>every 5 days</>.
·You <green>won't be able to switch equipment or Relics</> in the Wormhole, so get prepared before starting the challenge.
·Clear the current level and meet the Wanderer level requirement for the next level to unlock the next difficulty level.

xingjietansuo.ActivityDesc:
There are huge rifts that connect the distant cosmic planets in abnormal post-Cataclysm spaces. Through long-term observation, researchers found that these abnormal spaces are not as threatening as they seem.
Even so, they still need to be dealt with.

·<green>Every day,</> 6 <green>Star Gates</> appear somewhere in the world. Walk into a Star Gate to start a challenge in the Star Realm. 
·Defeat certain waves of enemies in the Star Realm to win rewards. <green>Starseeds</> may show up after the <green>final wave</> of enemies. Deconstruct them to summon a <green>hidden boss</>. Defeat the boss to obtain a bonus reward.

TreasureMap.ActivityDesc:
Omnium Beacon is an entertainment project developed by Crown Mines' Parliament in order to draw more business to the region. It uses beacons converted from ore detectors used in the mines.
Each beacon buried marks the start of an exciting zero-sum game!
 
· Claim Omnium collectors anytime at the cost of <green>30 VIT</> each time.
· If an Omnium collector is not retrieved by other Wanderers within a certain amount of time <green>(Blue: 24h, Purple: 24h, Orange: 24h)</>, the Wanderer who buried it will then be rewarded.
· Wanderers will also be rewarded if they use <green>Omnium signals</> to find and retrieve collectors placed by other Wanderers.

SoloLeague.ActivityDesc:
After its reorganization, the Martial Federation from the pre-Cataclysm days started to hold new one-on-one tournaments. Although the current tournaments are not comparable to the old ones in terms of scale, many battle elites are still drawn in.

· The league is a <green>balanced arena</> that allows Wanderers to compete at a similar level of basic stats to ensure fair play.
· <green>The battlefield shrinks over time</>, so Wanderers need to watch their step while fighting their opponents.
· The arena is available at 12:00–24:00 daily. By the end of each season, rewards will be granted according to Wanderers' <green>ranks</>. The higher the rank, the richer the reward. Become a legend on the battlefield!

WorldBoss.ActivityDesc:
After the Cataclysm, Hykros was forced to cut off contact with other regions. Omnium twisted the minds of almost all creatures. The frontier has fallen.
However, the transfer stations there have been under ever heavier assaults since then. Stop enemies from coming in before it grows into a greater crisis.

<green>Wanderers obtain 1 more challenge attempt respectively every Tuesday, Thursday, and Saturday, up to 3 attempts in total. Each battle lasts 8 minutes.</>
·Wanderers can get <green>buffs</> based on their <green>number of Crewmates</> in battle.

digong.ActivityDesc:
Ruins are facilities left by pre-Cataclysm residents, and you are definitely not the first to find them.
Be careful! The traps by previous residents and the force controlling this place aren't on your side!

Meet the <green>level requirement</> to enter the ruin.
Explore every difficulty level of the ruin to obtain rewards.

HookClone.ActivityDesc:
Before the Cataclysm, Federation scientists developed a virtual training ground for military purposes. Now, Hykros has successfully recovered the technology and built a virtual training space for all frontiers.
Come give it a go!

Wanderers can select from a variety of training. Maximum <green>4 people</> can match up/team up to take the challenge to win rewards.
Wanderers can unlock the training of a higher difficulty by reaching the required level.

Feed.ActivityDesc:
Tired of adventuring? Come and check out the dishes Mi-a has prepared for you!
– Mi-a

Every day after <green>05:00, 12:00, and 18:00</>, Wanderers will receive a chance to taste the food Mi-a has cooked.
Gifts and powerful buffs await!

RandomRuins.ActivityDesc:
Explore the ruin to uncover the traces of time.

<green>Spacetime Domain</> only allows solo challenges.
The ruins you enter depend on the <green>Dimension level</>. The higher the Dimension level, the more categories of ruins you will be qualified to enter.

VoidClone.ActivityDesc:
One of the unusual dimensional phenomena found after the Cataclysm. Observations revealed that the interior is comprised of various unknown mechanisms and traps.
Even without a large presence of dangerous hostiles, one still cannot be too careful.

Get one extra <green>challenge chance every Monday, Wednesday, and Friday. Save up to 3 times per week.</>
Gather <green>3 keys</> before time runs out to unlock the mechanism and open the exit.

tansuo.ActivityDesc:
Experience life on the land of Aesperia to enrich your adventure.
Explore areas on Aida. You may find the secrets of the world in unexpected places.

BigSecret.ActivityDesc: The newly-invented consciousness infiltration space by Hykros can extract the consciousness of an Executor and allow them to enter the consciousness of evil individuals such as the Hyenas and the Ravagers to break their aggressive consciousness and lower their overall aggression. However, it's highly risky, so please get prepared beforehand.

minigame.ActivityDesc:
The mini games provided by the training facility are like nutritious meals in the canteens: there are always several dishes for you to choose from every day.
They might seem dull, but these activities can train every part of your body and boost your health in the long run.

StaminaPush.PushMsgBody: Dear Wanderer, your vitality has reached the limit. Go on with your adventure!
